00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:38,400
heard you recommend. It's called 
signposting. What is signposting?

329
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:45,680
Signposting is using certain words, phrases, 
formatting, and an overall structure in  

330
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:53,520
your writing that helps guide your reader and 
signals what is coming in the rest of the post.  

331
00:27:53,520 --> 00:28:02,960
So, this is especially helpful if you have a long 
memo. It adds structure to where are we going and  

332
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:07,840
what certain sections of paragraphs are about. 
So some of my favorite signposting words are,  

333
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:12,720
"for example," shows that you're about to 
show an example because shows that you're  

334
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:19,040
about to share your logic and rationale behind 
something. "As a next step," is a great one.  

335
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:24,320
People's eyes automatically zoom to, "as a next 
step." Even "First, second, third," kicking off  

336
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:30,080
a paragraph with that, you're not needing to 
rely on rich text formatting with bolding,  

337
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:36,480
italics, underlines and all that craziness. If 
you kick off sentences with signposting words,  

338
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:40,960
you can often signal, "Here's what I'm 
about to talk about in this paragraph."

339
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:46,160
These are power words for clarity. There's 
this whole concept of power words like, "free."

340
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,480
Yeah. "A gift."

341
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:54,320
"Gift." Yeah. For copywriting and these are 
basically power words for helping your brain  

342
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:58,560
see the structure and get to the thing you want 
to pay attention to. So I'll read back the words  

343
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:05,200
you just used. "For example," " because," "as 
a next step," and then, "first, second, third."

344
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:11,440
Yeah. Yeah. You can use signposting in writing and 
