352
00:29:52,000 --> 00:30:03,760
I really hate excessive formatting. So, I've seen 
memos where 30% of the note was bolded. And that  

353
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:08,640
just negates the entire point of bolding because 
if everything is bolded then nothing is being  

354
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:13,120
highlighted, right? So I think using formatting 
in general more sparingly than you think you  

355
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:21,680
have to is probably a good rule of thumb. I also 
dislike when people overuse bullets and sentence  

356
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:27,840
fragments, phrases in bullets when they should 
use complete sentences that actually show the  

357
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:32,960
connected tissue between ideas, that show the 
logical flow of what it is that you're saying. 

358
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:41,040
And it feels faster and more concise to put 
bullets and fragments, but a lot of times  

359
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:47,920
your reader on the other end of that is needing to 
